To back up (export) a virtual machine:

Take ESXi out of maintenance mode:
In web GUI:  Host -> Actions -> Exit maintenance mode

Shut down the virtual machine if it is running.

In web GUI, under virtual machines:
Right click on virtual machine name.  Select "Export With Images".
Click "OK" to begin downloading the OVF file, MF file, NVRAM file, and VMDK
   image file.

Move downloaded files to desired backup server/directory and set desired
ownership/permissions.
